# hydrology local configuration (template)

Copy to your project as `hydrology.local.md` and fill in. Loaders and
workflows read this file; nothing here is a credential.

## Region and gauges

- Basin(s) of interest: <name, HUC if known>
- Reference gauges (near-natural; drought/climate work):
  <site numbers as strings, e.g. "09085000">
- Operational gauges (regulated; operations questions):
  <e.g. "09380000" (below Glen Canyon Dam), "09379900" (Lake Powell elevation)>
- SWOT continents/passes if known: <e.g. NA>

## Compute and volumes

- Download gate: 2 GB (loaders stop and ask above this)
- Cache directory: <path, e.g. ~/NWIS_cache, ~/SWOT_hydro>
- Compute scale available: small (laptop) | medium (Dask) | large

## Knowledge

- Extra concepts for this project: <paths or none>
- Climatology window for indices: 1991-2020 unless stated otherwise
- Endpoint convention for reservoir years: calendar unless stated
